urls.description: Norfolk-based artist Vanessa Lubach likens her printmaking practice to that of oil painting and draws on the latter to inform her vibrant compositions. "I linocut like a painter and paint like a linocutter, and the two disciplines work together to inform and enhance each other," she tells Colossal.
urls.title: Dozens of Carved Layers Compose Vivid Linocut Prints of Cats and Bouquets by Vanessa Lubach
